ce:section.ce:para:
The lung, liver and kidney sections were established using standard laboratory procedures, and then stained with hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) or ponceau 2R-acid fuchsin-aniline blue (Masson trichrome staining). All sections were evaluated using a light microscopy and images were taken. The Masson images were analyzed by the ImageJ software (version 1.53, https://imagej.nih.gov/ij/) to calculate the collagenvolume fraction (CVF) of each group based on randomly selected ten images. The analysis procedure is described below:

                              1)

Open ImageJ software, click File to open a Masson-stained image;


                              2)

Click Image, Color, Color Deconvolution and choose Masson Trichrome to separate red and blue regions;


                              3)

Click Image, Adjust, Threshold to select blue region (collagen part), and then click Analyze and Measure to get collagen area;


                              4)

Click Image, Adjust, Threshold again to select total tissue and measure the total tissue area;


                              5)

CVF= (collagen area/total tissue area) *100%

Since the association between ferroptosis and fibrosis has been reported by several studies (Xu et al., 2020), a specific ferroptosis inhibitor Fer-1 was used to evaluate the relationship of ferroptotic and fibrotic effects both induced by GQDs. We firstly confirmed that Fer-1 treatment significantly reversed the increased iron levels, lipid peroxidation and alternations on expressions of ferroptosis relevant proteins that all caused by GQDs, especially when the exposure dosage of GQDs is 1 mg/kg BW (Figs. S6 and S7). After that, the protective role of Fer-1 in the pulmonary, hepatic and renal fibrosis induced by GQDs was assessed. According to Masson staining images and CVF data, the areas or contents of collagenous fibers increased by 1 mg/kg BW N-GQDs and A-GQDs in lung and kidney tissues as well as that increased by 1 mg/kg BW N-GQDs were statistically significantly alleviated by Fer-1 (Fig. 6
                        ). However, not all increased expressions of p-Smad3 caused by 1 mg/kg BW N-GQDs and A-GQDs in lung and liver tissues were reversed by Fer-1, but only the enhancement in protein p-Smad3 expression in lung tissues of mice treated with N-GQDs was alleviated by Fer-1 (Fig. 7
                         and Fig. S8).
